{
  "texts": [
    "As shown in Fig. 2, through the learnable cooccurrence scoring module under the constraint of the consistency loss L cs, the cooccurrence \"counter\" is significantly highlighted to indicate the ground-truth action.",
    "D.3 Observation EnhancementTo encourage VLN agents to learn sufficient open-world alignment knowledge under the correctable landmark discovery framework, we design an observation enhancement strategy, where we use the corrected landmark feature f Ut = {f Ut,n } No n=1 and the original observation feature f Ot = {f Ot,n } No n=1 to obtain the enhanced observation features f ′ Ot = {f ′ Ot,n } No n=1 for action decision.",
    "Specifically, at timestep t, we calculate f Ut,n by:f Ut,n = p U la t,n • s la • f U la t + N co i=1 p U co t,i,n • s co i • f U co t,i,(15)where f U la t and f U co t,i are the textual features of the landmark U la t and the cooccurrence U co t,i.",
    "Through s la and s co i, the feature of the important cooccurrence can be highlighted.",
    "Then, we use f Ut,n and f Ot,n to obtain the enhanced observation feature f ′ Ot,n for O t,n:f ′ Ot,n = f Ot,n + f Ut,n."
  ]
}